Jim Walter Corp said its boardapproved a 5-for-4 stock split in the form of a 25 pct stockdividend to be distributed July 12 to stockholders of recordJune 15.    It also said its board approved a regular quarterly cashdividend of 35 cts a share on its pre-split common, payableJuly one to holders of record June 15. The current dividend isequal to 28 cts on the common outstanding after the split.    The company said it plans to increase the quarterly cashdividend on the post-split shares by seven pct to 30 ctsbeginning with the October one payment. Reuter&#3;